	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think the Honorable Naldiin did an excellent job condensing Iksar history.  There are a few holes that need to be filled in current events that I have questions about and can only speculate.<br><br>1.) How did the Iksar's become followers of Cazic Thule when it was certainly Innoruk(sp?) that gave them freedom with the coming of the Greenmist.  I'm assuming the makers of the Iksar where followers of the Lord of Fear and therefore the Iksar disposition is more apt to follow his leading.<br><br>2.) The troopers of Cabilis talk of the Emperor, but none have seen him or of this councel of five that is spoken of in the ancient texts.  The Necromancers seem to be the real power in Cabilis at the moment.  How did that happen?<br><br>3.) The test of betrayal within the SK guild for the Crusader's Khruki follows the events of an SK traitor who wishes to give ancient and holy texts to an agent of Mistmore.  The plan is stopped, but such dealings with Mistmore is a concern in the future considering the Necro's would be most likely to align with the ancient Vampire.<br><br>4.)  I am wondering if Innoruke(sp?...again)in the coming war will again claim the Iksar as his own and whether the Necro's will back him in his conquest of our race.  I do not think the SK guild would support this - Even though we use Necro spells, we are more aligned with the Shamans of our culture.<br><br>Okay...these are just wonderings on my part.  I do not know what the coming war will mean to my people, the Iksar, but I know it will be interesting to find out.<br><br>I'm sorry that I was not able to respond earlier, friend Tochail.  Thanks for the link and good hunting.<br>&nbsp;<br>Shrikke - Knight of Fear<br>Bristlebane</td></tr>
