<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100447314939093></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100447314939093><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=/poster.html?user=631&mid=100447314939093>RE: Further background Information</a> <a id=fs8 href=/poster.html?user=631&mid=100447314939093#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=20 width=20></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 30th 3:19 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It is said by many that we Iksar have an unnatural aversion to dragonkind.  It is said that we grow weak at the sight of Wurms.  Though I have not been to Mistmoor, I do not think we of the necromancers could be subverted by the vampire...  and he has allies... the drachnid that plague our homeland come to mind.<br><br>Think like this, dread knight;  we shall use the vampire and his ilk as we would use any dangerous weapon.  It is better to have such a weapon aimed at an enemy than at oneself, is it not so?<br><br>Never will the necromancers, and yes, I even believe never will the shadowknights or monks, allow the Iksar to become enslaved once more.  We of the necromancers freed our kind once, and we would not see them as slaves ever again.<br><br>Usula of the Wurmbane Clutch<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
